docs.lead_paragraph: Fireside Talk on Foreign Topics. Mr. CORDEN, the celebrated free-trader and member for the West Riding of Yorkshire, has sustained a severe domestic affliction in the death of his only son, who, at the age of 15, died while traveling in Germany. Few men possess the troansure of a happier and more beautiful home than that to which this breathing of the augel brings such a sorrow.

docs.lead_paragraph: To Hon; John P. Hale: DEAR SIR; Observing that you have promptly repelled a slander recently uttered on the floor of the Senate, I avail myself of the occasion to vindicate both myself and my follow-citizens of New-England from unfounded and injurious imputations. In doing this I am influenced solely by a regard for truth and by respect for the Senate of my country.
